commitResults.messageTitle: Update all files in dukepro package
commitResults.messageBody:
There were many checkstyle errors at first.

All dheckstyle errors have been resolved except for "unused javadoc tag" because every method should have a javadoc tag thus I did not delete any so called "unused java doc" tags

Change gradle build to reflect latest changes

After using JavaFX the main package is now renamed to "dukepro" rather than "duke".

Updating these changes in build.gradle tells shadowjar how to build the new .jar file

In order to do this, te archiveBaseName was changed from "duke" to "dukepro" to reflect the latest package and mainClassName is now "dukepro.Launcher"

Assert is not added in this project

Assert should be added so that the programmer can spot his or her errors more easily

Added some asserts in the dukepro.handlers.Decoder and dukepro.handlers.Interact.

The aforementioned classes are responsible for handling user input, and throwing errors when users provide bad input. The programmer may handle errors and parse inputs wrongly so these classes need assert to be added

commitResults.messageBody:
A generic Storage class is required for  the expenses manager, so it is as extensible as possible.

Create a StorableaObjects class to abstract away storing details.

Internal implementation of Storage class needs to be changed.

Generic Managers and Storage classes are required to make the code more extensible

Replace TaskManager with a generic Manager and the Storage in TaskManager with a GeneralStorage.

Need to replace ExpenseManager with new generic Manager class.

ExpenseManager field of Interact needed to be replaced with a generic Manager class.

Replace ExpenseManager in Interact with a generic Manager. Delete irrelevant classes like Storage, TaskManager, ExpenseManager

Need to implement a class or method that tabulates all expenses.

Currently unable to tabulate total costs for all expenses

Add ExpenseCalculator class to support this functionality.

More specific functions can be a part of ExpenseCalculator in future, such as date specific functions etc.

Need to update ExpenseCalculator so support action where user wants to know how much was spent in a day.

Add spentDay method to ExpenseCalculator so that user can find how much he / she has spent on a particular day.

User can now find out how much has been spent on a particular day by writing "spentDate" followed by the Date in YYYY-MM-DD format into the GUI.

Javadocs was not updated to reflect the latest changes

Update Javadocs to reflect new functions and classes.

The code passes the checkstyle tests.

Not all StorableObjects require a "done" boolean field. Expenses are not "done".

Rather than having a "markAsDone" method in Manager, use the operationOnList method of the Manager class to handle the operation

May need to revamp updated code to be more OOP
